# PCONFIG (Peripheral Configuration Library) Configuration

menuconfig PCONFIG
	bool "PCONFIG (Peripheral Configuration Library)"
	default n
	depends on OSAL
	help
	  Peripheral Configuration Library selects a platform configuration
	  backend and exposes normalized hardware configuration to LPF kernel
	  services.

	  PCONFIG describes the physical hardware configuration of a platform
	  (board variant, peripheral connections, pin mappings, etc.) in a
	  structured, data-driven way.

	  Key features:
	  - Platform-specific hardware descriptions
	  - Backend-based configuration loading
	  - Device Tree backend for SoC/product board descriptions
	  - Built-in static product tables
	  - Normalized peripheral configuration list
	  - Query-only platform configuration API for consumers

	  Memory footprint: small code footprint + product configuration data

	  Use cases:
	  - Fixed product hardware descriptions
	  - Multi-board product variants selected by a PCONFIG backend
	  - Hardware configuration for LPF peripheral services
	  - Peripheral lookup by index or platform/product name

	  Dependencies: OSAL (for basic services)

	  Note: Enable OSAL first in "Core Modules" menu.
	  LPF peripheral services must not depend on concrete product table symbols
	  or backend implementations.

	  Recommended: Enable for products with hardware configuration tables

	  If unsure, say Y.
